post_text: My heart breaks today as I learn of the passing of one of my patients, gone way too soon. I‚Äôll never forget the first time Monte Michael walked through my front door. I had only been open a couple of months at the time. Panic and anxiety sunk in as I recalled all of his past injuries throughout the years (this man literally had gone through his nine lives). I was SO Nervous to treat him, hoping I wouldn‚Äôt hurt him. After my initial visit with him, he walked out of my office feeling better than he had in a long time. My dad was sitting at my front desk on his lunch break. I walked over to him and told him, ‚ÄúIf there is absolutely no other person I help in this world, I hope I help him!‚Äù The one person that had exhausted all other treatment options. Over time, I developed a wonderful personal relationship with Monte. I will forever miss our chats about Big Bucks, and working hard, and earning people‚Äôs respect. Monte was one of a kind! He‚Äôll always hold a special place in my heart. Rest Easy my friend! ‚ù§Ô∏è ü¶å

post_text: I‚Äôm sharing this in hope of spreading awareness to potentially save a life. A Deep Vein Thrombosis (DVT) is a blood clot that commonly forms in a vein in the leg. It is Characterized by pain swelling, or tenderness of the leg, sometimes with warmth or redness. Risk factors include: prolonged bed rest, recent surgery, pregnancy, obesity, smoking, cancer, heart failure (even people who have Atrial Fibrillation), etc. A Pulmonary Embolism occurs when a blood clot breaks loose and travels to the lungs. This is characterized by a shortness of breath, sharp rib/chest pain, and even light-headedness. However, may have a DVT and experience NO signs or symptoms. This is a life-threatening emergency and nothing to be taken lightly. Please seek medical attention immediately!

post_text:
ATTENTION: ALL Men!
Are u suffering from chronic back pain? Could your wallet be the culprit?

Millions of guys drive or sit all day with their wallet in their back pocket, but they can't figure out why they moan whenever they get out of the car. But sitting on your wallet while you drive is a recipe for lower back pain and - if you do it often enough -- nerve pain that shoots down your leg. Riding with one cheek higher than other can trigger chronic pain in your back, hips, and shoulders. It can even set off foot cramps.

Sitting on your wallet throws off your alignment and compresses the sciatic nerve, which runs from each side of the spine down through the back of each thigh to the foot. A compressed sciatic nerve causes searing leg pain and numbness called sciatica.

But the fix is simple: Get that wallet out of your back pocket!
